TELC:sample.name: PS
TELC:sample.TELC:description: This is not applicable to MTL as Media does not have dedicated FIVR/DLVR. Notes from previous products(TGL/ADL): The FIVR PS, to be sent to FIVR HIP. If 000, PCU will calculate the PS value to sample to TV, based on cutoff registers (IO_FIVR_PS_GT_UNSLICE). If non-zero, then this is the TV. Note that if cutoff register is all zero, the result is zero, hence pcode have full control. Encoding is: 000 to 100 are PS0/PS1/PS2/PS3/PS4, active states selected by cutoffs. PS5/PS6 are special. 111=PS7 is OFF state, which we are allowed to use each time both voltage/current are both zero.
